{
  "texts": [
    "This aligns with the findings of Awni et al. [92].In a concept similar to ensemble learning, Poznanski and Wolf [95] introduced a multibranch VGG16 architecture.",
    "Unlike using one FC layer for the entire attribute architecture, the authors employed separate FCs for each attribute.",
    "This design capitalizes on CLs' ability to recognize letter appearances independently of their position, while FCs capture spatial information.",
    "Dividing the single FC layer into parts, each corresponding to a spatial section, enables specialized learning, ultimately enhancing accuracy.",
    "The model, tested on diverse databases, including IFN/ENIT for Arabic, delivered results ranging from 94.09% to 99.29% accuracy depending on the test scenario."
  ]
}